.SH NAME
.P
rfd - rushfind file finder with GNU-find-oriented syntax and parallel traversal
.P
.SH SYNOPSIS
.P
\fBrfd\fR [\fIglobal-options\fR] [\fIpath\fR .\&.\&.\&] [\fIexpression\fR]
.P
.SH DESCRIPTION
.P
\fBrfd\fR is the installed command for \fBrushfind\fR, a Rust implementation of Unix
\fBfind\fR(1) that keeps a GNU-oriented command line while adding a parallel
traversal engine.\&
.P
If no \fIpath\fR arguments are given, \fBrfd\fR searches the current directory.\& If no
\fIexpression\fR is given, \fBrfd\fR behaves as if -print had been supplied.\&
.P
Expression parsing follows GNU \fBfind\fR(1) precedence:
.P
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.IP \(bu 4
.\}
Adjacent primaries imply -a.\&
.RE
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.IP \(bu 4
.\}
-a binds tighter than -o.\&
.RE
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.IP \(bu 4
.\}
